<TITLE> Moon sighting committee to sit at 6.30pm </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, September 30 (bdnews24.com)The National Moon Sighting Committee is scheduled to sit Tuesday evening to decide the day on which Eid-ul-Fitr will be celebrated. The meeting, chaired by law adviser AFM Hassan Ariff, will sit at the Islamic Foundation from 6:30pm. Anyone sighting the Shawal moon has been requested by the Islamic Foundation to notify them by telephone on: 9559493, 9556407, 9559643, 9555951, 9555947 and 9558337; or send a fax to 9563397. Muslims round off their month long Ramadan fast by celebrating and offering special prayers on the Eid day. bd
